<div class='center'>
  <h3 class='col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 center home_section_header '>Features</h3>
</div>

<div class='header-section col-xs-12'></div>

<div class='row '>
<div class='features_container section_block col-md-10 col-md-offset-2 col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1'>
  <div class="section_body">
    <div class='feature_item'>
      <div class='feature_item_main_header'>
        1. Translation Channel
      </div>
      <img class="col-md-5 col-xs-12" src="<%= asset_path("translator_profiles.png") %>" style='height: 400px;'>
      <div class='col-md-5 col-xs-12 feature_description_container'>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Viewership</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>Manage your very own translation channel where you can track shares, views, and comments. Your channel also lists your past work, allowing viewers to easily see what you've done before.  
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Increase Traffic to Uploader</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>Because we use softsubs, in which subtitles are simply overlayed to the original video, all the traffic that goes to your subtitles also goes to the original youtube video - thus supporting the original video owner.</span>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Go Live instantly</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>No longer do you have to go through the lengthy process of download, re-encode, and re-upload. All you need is a youtube link, then you can start adding subtitles using our online editor, hit publish, and it'll go live instantly.</span>
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class='feature_item'>
      <div class='feature_item_main_header'>
        2. Player
      </div>
      <img class="col-md-5 col-xs-12" src="<%= asset_path("video_comments.png") %>">
      <div class='col-md-5 col-xs-12 feature_description_container'>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Share & Embed</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>Created subtitles can be shared and embedded in external sites. </span>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Comments</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>Users can also add comments to the subtitle video, thus providing feedback to translators who help subtitle them</span>
      </div>
      
    </div>
    <div class='feature_item'>
      <div class='feature_item_main_header'>
        3. Inline Corrections
      </div>
      <img class="col-md-5 col-xs-12" src="<%= asset_path("correct_line.png") %>">
      <div class='col-md-5 col-xs-12 feature_description_container'>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Suggest Changes</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>Anyone can suggest changes to a subtitle directly on the transcript. The subtitlers would get notified of any correction requests sent and they can approve/reject them in one-click. </span>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Contribution Profile</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>The more corrections you contribute, the more points you'll receive. You'll also be able to see the list of corrections you've sent and received.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class='feature_item'>
      <div class='feature_item_main_header'>
        4. Topics
      </div>
      <img class="col-md-5 col-xs-12" src="<%= asset_path("group_page.png") %>">
      <div class='col-md-5 col-xs-12 feature_description_container'>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Collaborate</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>For bigger projects with lots of videos, translators can collaborate with each other and form a topic where people can easily access subtitles that have been created.</span>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Request Subtitles</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>Viewers can request subtitles that's related to the topic</span>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Publish and Subscribe</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>Anyone who subscribes to the topic will get notified whenever a subtitle has been released for the group. </span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class='feature_item'>
      <div class='feature_item_main_header'>
        5. Add Subtitles Back to Youtube
      </div>
      <img class="col-md-5 col-xs-12" src="<%= asset_path("official_page.png") %>">
      <div class='col-md-5 col-xs-12 feature_description_container'>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Add Subtitles back to Youtube</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>The original video owner can easily import user submitted translations with one-click. One only needs to link their youtube account(s) to find all user translations made for their videos.</span>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>International Fans</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>Viewers who subtitle a youtuber's videos and share it with their followers would help reach out to international fans and increase their youtube traffic at the same time.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class='feature_item'>
      <div class='feature_item_main_header'>
        6. Subtitle Editor
      </div>
      <img class="col-md-5 col-xs-12" src="<%= asset_path("editor_view.png") %>">
      <div class='col-md-5 col-xs-12 feature_description_container'>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Multiple Views</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>One can toggle between 'Timeline' and 'Subtitle' view. Timeline offers a more graphical interface for adjusting start and end times of a subtitle, while the 'Subtitle' view gives a more familiar list view that provides easier navigation of the entire subtitle.</span>
        <h3 class='feature_item_header'>Upload Existing Subtitles</h3>
        <span class='feature_description'>Sometimes, translators prefer to use other editors such as Aegisub. In those cases, they can create the subtitles using their own tools and later upload them to the online editor.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>

<div class='header-section col-xs-12'></div>
